<P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#000000><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uigronimus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>igronimus</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Forum Apprentice</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>5/4/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>10:12:38 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: MASTERS OF DD??? Bah, Absor has a new &quot;vision&quot;</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">There was no 'creative editing' involved in my quote of absor.  What I posted he said verbatim.  I left out the whole druid part because it wasn't really important, aside from the fact that making us better transporters is somehow supposed to balance us with a class that can nuke second best, heal, dot, sow, buff, port and wear decent armor.<br>
<br>
As far as reading into something, ....  I really don't think that's the case.<br>
<br>
ABSOR:  &quot;Regardless of past perceptions or texts or class descriptions, Wizards are becoming masters of teleportation.&quot;<br>
<br>
druid blabbering (look back if you want to read it, someone posted it)<br>
<br>
&quot;Yes, we are moving toward making Wizards the master of arcane transportation. This seems like the right direction to take the class.&quot;<br>
<br>
What are the past perceptions and class descriptions of wizards?  Master of DD, it's right in the EQ manual.  It's what wizards have been touting as their reason to make us better at it for the past year and in all the balance threads.  If Absor comes out and says that this is no longer the case, regardless of what Verant said in the past or we thought we used to be, and that they have a new direction (the 'right direction' according to him), making us masters of teleportation, that means to me EXACTLY what is sounds like, regardless of what the question was that he was responding to.<br>
<br>
Aside from the Bane spells, our DD has NOT been improved.  Our concerns about DD issues have not even been formally addressed by him.  Absor recently stated our new direction is becoming MASTERS of TRANSPORTATION, regardless of past statements.   In light of all this, it seems pretty clear to me where we are headed, and if you believe otherwise I sincerely think you're being overly optimistic.<br>
<br>
Don't get me wrong, I like my class, I really don't think I could enjoy another class as much as my wizard.  But, frankly, I'm to the point where I'm just plain PISSED off at Verant, we've pointedly ignored and set aside for quite a long time, if not the history of the class.  I'm sick of getting cheap bones thrown to me like translocates and harvests and level 60 DDs I'll prolly never see, while the real issues are being ignored.  I don't even really care any more if they don't fix us, but at least have the decency to come out and admit you're not gonna fix us, although what Absor just stated is pretty damn close to that.<br>
</font><P><hr>
